  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Infection Prevention and Control (IPC) through safe Water Supply, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) in Targeted Frontline Healthcare Facilities and public places.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this application is to contribute towards minimizing risks of EVD transmission at selected health facilities and public places through IPC and WASH support in case of the spreading of the disease from DRC. With this CERF grant, UNICEF will procure and distribute WASH IPC supplies to 50 health facilities, will establish an EVD screening area in these health facilities, and train 50 staff of these facilities on Infection Prevention Control (IPC) measures. The project will last six months and will benefit 135,000 people including 78,300 women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
